    <tags>screenshot capture annotation tray productivity</tags>
    <summary>Fast screenshots with annotations — tray-resident, hotkey-driven, free.</summary>
    <description>
Kashot is a fast, free, tray-resident screenshot tool with a built-in annotation editor.

* Tray-resident, single-instance, single-binary install.
* Global hotkey (default PrintScreen) opens a region selector across all monitors.
* Nine annotation tools: pen, line, arrow, rectangle, ellipse, marker, text, numbered step, blur/pixelate.
* Four colour palettes (Vivid / Highlighter / Pastel / Pro).
* Save, copy to clipboard, or pin to screen as an always-on-top window.
* Optional watermark on saved images.
* No telemetry, no accounts, source on GitHub.

Native on Windows. Native Linux and macOS builds available via the Rust port (kashot-rs).
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/singhpratech/kashot/releases/tag/v0.4.1</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
